            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " 5.E+9 nthermal/(cm2*sec)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The fissile materials from 0.5 ug/cm2 to 100 ug/cm2",
                " according to their fission cross section, were",
                " evaporated onto thin backings."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two collimated PI*cm2 surface-barrier detectors",
                "were placed symmetrically at 3.5 cm on both sides of",
                "the sample.",
                "For complementary fragments detection."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The two complementary fragment pulse heights and",
                "time-of-flight difference between the two fragments",
                "were recorded event by event."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The pulse heights were converted into fragment",
                "provisional masses and kinetic energies through an",
                "iterative procedure using:",
                "-  of Schmitt+,",
                "- U-235 and Cf-252 calibration data,",
                "- mass and momentum conservation relations.",
                " Total excitation energy of the system E* was",
                "determined: E* = Qmax - TKE, where",
                "Qmax - maximum Q-value of the reaction,",
                "TKE - the final kinetic energy of the fragments."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REL-REF": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "M",
